<H3> <TI>   One Arrested, 2,250 Grams of Cocaine Seized at Beirut Airport </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    One Arrested, 2,250 Grams of Cocaine Seized at Beirut Airport </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0306190794 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1115 GMT 3 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0306190794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This morning customs officials at Beirut airport 
foiled an attempt to smuggle a quantity of drugs into Lebanon. 
  Husayn 'Ali al-Sahili, born in 1973 in Kafr Zabad in 
al-Biqa', was arrested upon his arrival from Colombia via 
Amsterdam, and 2,250 grams of cocaine were seized with him. The 
drugs were hidden in an innovative and technical way--inside a 
case with a false bottom and inside two nylon envelopes. The 
case passed, undetected, through X-ray machines in European 
airports. Al-Sahili was arrested and referred to the 
counternarcotics office. 
  The local value of the seized drug was estimated at $70,000 
and estimated at $5,000 in Colombia. 

</TEXT>

