<F P=100> AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> NIGERIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   NDLEA Draws Up `Master Plan' To Fight `Hard' Drugs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NDLEA Draws Up `Master Plan' To Fight `Hard' Drugs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB3105105794 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network in English 2100 GMT 
30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB3105105794 </F>
<F P=104>  Lagos Radio Nigeria Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Drug Law Enforcement Agency, NDLEA, has 
drawn up a master plan to involve all Nigerians in the fight 
against hard drugs. The chairman of the agency, Brigadier 
General Musa Bamayi, gave the information today in Lagos when he 
led members of the task force on hard drugs on a courtesy visit 
to the Federal Radio Corporation of Nigeria, FRCN. 
  Brig Gen. Bamayi stated that the primary focus of the master 
plan would be on prevention to stop Nigerians from becoming drug 
addicts. He said that arrangements were being finalized to 
enable media representatives to monitor the activities of NDLEA 
as part of efforts to demonstrate that the agency would not 
operate in secrecy in its assignments. 
  Responding, the executive director of FRCN Lagos national 
station, Mr. Ikenna Ndaguba, who received the team on behalf of 
the director general, Alhaji Abdulraman Michika, stressed the 
importance of the media in prosecuting the drug war. He pledged 
the continued cooperation of Radio Nigeria in reaching the 
public effectively with antidrug programs of the agency. 

</TEXT>

