<F P=101> KAZAKHSTAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Asanbayev Meets With UN Leader Giacomelli, Discusses </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Asanbayev Meets With UN Leader Giacomelli, Discusses </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Combatting   Drug Smuggling 

<F P=102> LD2905055594 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 0400 GMT 
28 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2905055594 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>
BFN 

  [Text] Vice President Yerik Asanbayev received yesterday 
Giorgio Giacomelli, UN deputy secretary general and executive 
director of the UN fund for drug abuse. Under discussion was 
the issue of combatting drug smuggling. Giorgio Giacomelli said 
new sovereign states that appeared on the world's map after the 
break-up of the USSR are now turning into drug dealing centers. 
They also discussed the UN policy with regard to this issue. 
The vice president spoke about Kazakhstan's vision of its 
participation in the UN programme. Yerik Asanbayev emphasized 
that drug smuggling has to be addressed urgently. He said 
Kazakhstan has turned into a drug trading center, but does not 
have the equipment and experts to combat it. Therefore 
Kazakhstan would be grateful for any assistance that could be 
rendered to it by international organizations. This year 
Kazakhstan plans to send its envoy to Vienna who will deal with 
this issue. Kazakhstan is willing to cooperate with the United 
Nations in tackling this issue. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-45335 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "jptdd025__l94087" </HT>


