<H3> <TI>   Nearly One Tonne of Cocaine Paste Seized in San Martin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nearly One Tonne of Cocaine Paste Seized in San Martin </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Department 

<F P=102>   PY1006005394 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2024 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY1006005394 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>
BFN 

  [Text] Lima, 8 June (EFE) -- Peruvian security forces today 
seized almost one tonne of cocaine paste in San Martin 
Department, located in the jungle region. 
  A police source reported that the cocaine shipment was 
seized 
during a Peruvian Police Antidrug Division (Dirandro) operation 
conducted in the town of San Hilarion, in Bellavista Province. 
  San Martin and Bellavista are located in the Huallaga 
valley, 
the largest cocaine paste producing center in the world. 
  The police spokesman reported that during the operation, the 
police arrested three drug traffickers who were in charge of 
guarding the shipment. He established that they were two 
Peruvians and once Colombian, but their identities have not been 
disclosed. 

</TEXT>

