<H3> <TI>   6,000 Kg of Hashish, 557 Kg of Opium Seized in Herat Province </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    6,000 Kg of Hashish, 557 Kg of Opium Seized in Herat Province </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706201594 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 
GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706201594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Pashto </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Security officials of Herat Province yesterday 
seized 6,000 kilograms of hashish and 557 kilograms of opium. A 
source from the south-western zone told the BAKHTAR INFORMATION 
AGENCY that the drugs, placed in small bags and transported by 
two motor vehicles, were captured by officials of the Jehadi 
21st Division of Shindand District. Six carriers in the case 
were captured with 1,500,000 afghanis and were handed over to 
legal sources for investigation. The source said the captured 
drugs were taken to Herat, and the consuls of Iran, Saudi Arabia 
and Turkmenistan, a number of domestic and foreign reporters, 
and officials of Herat Province inspected the drugs in Herat. 

</TEXT>

