  [Text] Frauenfeld, 7 June -- On Monday, two Turkish 
citizens carried out a drugs deal involving 3 kg of heroin a few 
meters away from the police station in Weinfeld. They were 
observed by the police and arrested. The Thurgau Investigations 
Office and police said on Tuesday that they had received 
information from Germany and Austria that the two arrested 
persons were dealers in weapons and drugs. The Thurgau 
authorities undertook investigations together with the Criminal 
Office of the land of Baden-Wuerttemberg. When it transpired 
that drugs were going to be sold, the criminal and security 
police entered a shop owned by one of the two Turks and arrested 
both of them. They are suspected of organized crime. One of 
them was recently convicted by the District Court of 
Bischofszell of possessing a few hundred grams of heroin. He 
has lodged an appeal. 

