<F P=100> CENTRAL EURASIA </F>
<F P=101> RUSSIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opium Factory Shut Down, Two Dealers Arrested in Moscow Raid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opium Factory Shut Down, Two Dealers Arrested in Moscow Raid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0606140594 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 3 Jun 94 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> PM0606140594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the rubric "Criminal Diary": </F>
"Shosse Entuziastov Leads to Drugs Den"] 
  [Text] The "laboratory" where the narcotics were 
manufactured ceased operations after the arrival there of staff 
from the Balashikha Internal Affairs Directorate. It was housed 
in an apartment in a block on the Shosse Entuziastov. 
  In the apartment they discovered eight kg of poppy stems, 
several liters of solution, a large quantity of syringes, and 
all kinds of devices for boiling, roasting, pounding, and 
grinding the material. They also found several batches ready 
for use. When the agents saw these things they decided to set 
up an ambush and waited in the apartment. 
  A few minutes later a young man from the Caucasus region 
entered the apartment. He was carrying 20 kg of poppy stems and 
1.5 liters of solution. He and the owner of the apartment, a 
23-year old local man, were taken to a remand center. Many 
local youngsters may have used the services of the drugs 
laboratory. An investigation is being carried out. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

