<F P=100> CENTRAL EURASIA </F>
<F P=101> MOLDOVA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Number of Drug Patients Reportedly Increasing 70 Percent Per </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Number of Drug Patients Reportedly Increasing 70 Percent Per </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Year 

<F P=102>   AU1106182894 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2000 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1106182894 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 9/6/1994 -- About 12,000 
patients are currently under the observation of the Chisinau 
City Narcotics Department, their number increasing at a rate of 
70 percent per year, declared at a session of the Mayor's Office 
Vasile Galearschi, chief of the city Department for Health Care, 
cited the newspaper CURIERUL DE SEARA. A similar 70-percent 
increase, compared to the first three months of last year was 
registered in the number of cases concerning patients suffering 
from drug-related psychoses. Over the past three years the 
number of cases of drug and other toxic substances addiction has 
risen 2.9 times. Galearschi specified that the City Narcotics 
Department cannot work at its full capacity because of its 
disastrous material situation, in the absence of a specialized 
narcotics unit. According to a decision of the Chisinau Mayor's 
Office, the program of social-economic development for Chisinau 
stipulates the construction of a narcotics unit in 1995, stated 
the cited source. 

</TEXT>

