<F P=100> LATIN AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> ST. LUCIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police, Inmates Destroy `Large Quantity' of Confiscated </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police, Inmates Destroy `Large Quantity' of Confiscated </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Drugs   in May 

<F P=102> FL1406111594 Castries HTS Caribvision Television in English 
1945 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1406111594 </F>
<F P=104>  Castries HTS Caribvision Television </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>
BFN 

  [Text] St. Lucia, like all the other countries in the 
region, continues to fight off the drug menace. As is 
customary, large quantities of drugs confiscated are set to the 
torch, hoping that this and the fines and imprisonment terms can 
act as a deterrent for both perpetrators and would-be felons. 
Last month, members of the Royal St. Lucia Police Force, 
accompanied by prison inmates, took a large quantity of 
confiscated drugs to the dump site and set it alight. The 
stash, comprising marijuana, cocaine, and crack, was estimated 
at over EC$250,000. 

</TEXT>

