<H3> <TI>   Envoys in DPRK Unsure of Joint Venture's Role in Heroin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Envoys in DPRK Unsure of Joint Venture's Role in Heroin </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Smuggling   Case 

<F P=102> LD1706131394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0725 
GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1706131394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Valiyev] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, 17 June -- Representatives of the Russian 
Embassy and trade mission in the DPRK had difficulty answering 
questions from an ITAR-TASS correspondent about the activities 
of "Monolit," a Russian-North Korean joint venture. They said 
that they were unaware of such an enterprise as it had never 
come up before. On 9 June several employees of the joint 
venture were caught redhanded trying to smuggle eight kg of 
heroin, worth a million dollars, into Russia. 
  One of the sources suggested to ITAR-TASS that the venture 
might be one of those which is sometimes created by DPRK 
representatives in the Russian Federation without going through 
Russian legal processes. Knowledge of such joint ventures is, 
as a rule, confined to an extremely small circle of trusted 
people. 

