<F P=100> CENTRAL EURASIA </F>
<F P=101> KAZAKHSTAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Interior Ministry Holds Antidrug Meeting in Zhambyl Oblast </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interior Ministry Holds Antidrug Meeting in Zhambyl Oblast </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406101394 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 0800 GMT 
14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1406101394 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Kazakh Interior Ministry held an itinerant 
session in the village of Tolebi, Zhambyl oblast, devoted to 
curbing drug trafficking. As is widely known, cannabis grown in 
Zhambyl oblast is used to produce the most widely spread drugs 
hashish and marijuana. The session noted that drugs smuggling 
routes connect the Chu valley of South Kazakhstan with China, 
India, Afghanistan, Italy, and France. New methods in the 
battle against drugs smugglers were discussed. 

</TEXT>

