<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Issues Communique on Tape Recordings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Ministry Issues Communique on Tape Recordings </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2206043394 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Canal 
A Network in Spanish 0235 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2206043394 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Canal 
A Network </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "CMI Newscast"] </F>
  [Text] The Ministry of Defense tonight issued a communique 
detailing the information the government received on the 
recordings. At approximately 1730 on Thursday, 16 June, Dr. 
Andres Pastrana and Dr. Luis Alberto Moreno paid a visit to the 
president and minister of defense and presented them with a tape 
containing three telephone conversations. The first two 
conversations were allegedly between journalist Alberto Giraldo 
and Mr. Miguel Orejuela and the third conversation was between 
Giraldo and Mr. Gilberto Rodriguez Orejuela. 
  Dr. Pastrana said he received the tape in the city of Cali 
the day before from people who did not identify themselves. 
Early on 17 June, the minister of defense, at the request of 
the president of the Republic, ordered the military forces 
general command and the police general directorate to confirm 
the veracity of voices and forward, as soon as possible, the 
tape and results of voice confirmation to the Prosecutor 
General's Office. The same order was given to the DAS 
[Administrative Department of Security] director. 
  After informing the prosecutor general, that same 17 June 
Dr. 
Ernesto Samper Pizano was informed about this situation and a 
copy of the tape was forwarded to him. At about 1630 on 17 
June, at the request of the defense minister, three Armed Forces 
commanders delivered the recording personally to the prosecutor 
general. The results of the confirmation of voices were 
forwarded first on Friday and then on Saturday. 
  Taking into consideration that this investigation falls 
under 
the Prosecutor General's Office, the government immediately 
forwarded the tapes and the voice confirmation to that agency. 
Additionally and as is routine, the government and Armed Forces 
are ready to assist the Prosecutor General's Office in all 
support needed in this case. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

