<H3> <TI>   Law Penalizing Poppy Growing Goes Into Effect </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Law Penalizing Poppy Growing Goes Into Effect </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2406221194 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1518 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY2406221194 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Lima, 24 Jun (EFE) -- A law establishing prison 
sentences of eight to 15 years for people who grow 
heroin-producing poppies went into effect in Peru today. 
  The law was approved by Congress on 22 June. It confirms the 
sentences included in the original bill. 
  The Peruvian penal code now includes the "crime of growing, 
promoting, assisting, or financing" the planting of poppy 
plantations used for making opium or heroin. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

